  <p class="article-lede">On March 10, the Ghana Stock Exchange Composite Index (GSE-CI) breached 15,000 for the first time in the exchange's history. By March 27, it had fallen to 12,990. More than GHS 55 billion in market capitalisation was erased in days. The correction was not caused by an economic crisis. It was caused by the structure of the rally itself.</p>

  <p>This article traces what drove the rally, what triggered the reversal, why the cocoa crisis may be connected, and what four scenarios look like from here. Every claim is sourced to verified market data.</p>

  <h2 id="what-happened">What Happened</h2>

  <div class="data-box">
    <h4>Key Numbers</h4>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
